item.title: SAT's Tomorrow
item.dc:creator: @BobDole81 BobDole81
item.description:
@BobDole81 wrote:

With a raw score of 0 in a specific subject, you’re score is 200 since if you get a negative raw score, it will deduct from that. They do that because for every correct answer you receive a point toward your raw score, but for each wrong answer you lose 1/4 point. If you don’t sign your name, you don’t get a score, so you don’t receive 200 points merely for that.

So 1210 is a pretty good score…the generally accepted average is 500 per SAT topic, and a 1210 would be an average of 605 each…

And @xxlegitxx: Please calm down and quit flaming…its not necessary.
